HEADWORD: Jacobinism
<hw>Jac"o*bin*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>Jacobinisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The principles of the Jacobins;
violent and factious opposition to legitimate government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Under this new stimulus, Burn's previous Jacobitism passed towards
the opposite, but not very distant, extreme of
<qex>Jacobinism</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J. C. Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

